cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of image retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves clustering of image features, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.MM) and data mining (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF), which are both techniques commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
